HEADWORD: Merrily
<hw>Mer"ri*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Merry</er>.]</ety> <def>In a merry manner; with mirth; with gayety
and laughter; jovially. See <er>Mirth</er>, and
<er>Merry</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Merrily</qex> sing, and sport, and play.</q>
<rj><qau>Granville.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

